    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p class="description">
      Kinematics is the study of motion. It focuses not on the forces that cause motion, but on the relationships between
      position, velocity, acceleration, and time. For example, given a ball rolling on a surface, kinematics can tell you
      its velocity at certain points, how far it travels in a given time, or its acceleration. In AP Physics 1, kinematics
      problems typically assume constant acceleration and use simple algebraic relationships known as the
      <em>kinematic equations</em>.
    </p>

    <div class="slideshow-container">
      <div class="slide">
