    </div>

    <h2>Summary of Kinematic Equations</h2>
    <div class="equations">
      1. v = v₀ + a·t<br>
      2. x = x₀ + v₀·t + ½·a·t²<br>
      3. v² = v₀² + 2·a·(x - x₀)<br>
      4. x = ½·(v + v₀)·t
    </div>

    <p class="description" style="margin-top:20px;">
      These four equations describe motion under constant acceleration and allow you to predict position, velocity, or time
      based on known variables.
    </p>

